  "text": "While the problem of transferring human expertise into computer programs was (at least partially) solved, it was discovered that the knowledge acquisition problem had been incorrecdy stated, right from the beginning. One piece of evidence for that is: Even after the successful construction of an operational rule-base, the meaning of the individual rules remained a mystery [CITATION_1] p. 241) . The maintenance of larger expert systems was consequently impossible. Since such systems were found to have several other disturbing deficiencies (e.g. brittleness), the definition of knowledge acquisition needed to be changed.",
